SIMPLE: misrule
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misrule
<hw>Mis*rule"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To rule
badly; to misgovern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misrule</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Misrule
<hw>Mis*rule"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act, or the
result, of misruling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disorder; confusion; tumult from
insubordination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Enormous riot and <qex>misrule</qex> surveyed.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Abbot of Misrule</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Lord of Misrule</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See under <er>Abbot</er>,
and <er>Lord</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misruly</ent>⟦br⟧
